What is difference between path and classpath variables?
1.PATH is the environment variable where we specify the locations of binaries.
Example: We add bin directory path of JDK or JRE, so that any binaries under the directory can be accessed directly without specifying absolute path.
2.CLASSPATH is the path for Java application where the classes you compiled will be available.
