what is Access Specifier?
An access specifier is a defining code element that can determine which elements of a program are allowed to access a specific variable or other piece of data.
What is OOP ? Define each feature of java OOP.
(OOP): is the dominant programming paradigm these days, having replaced the  procedural programming techniques
features:
1.Abstraction:  means displaying only essential information and hiding the details.
2.Encapsulation: is about how to hide data
3.Inheritance:is the process by which one object acquires the properties of another object.
4.Polymorphism: Polymorphism is the ability of an object to take on many forms.
