What is method overloading and when it happens?
Method overloading happens with methods with the same name but different signature. Method overriding happens with methods with the same name and same signature between inherited classes.
Explain exceptions in java and how to handle it.
An exception (or exceptional event) is a problem that arises during the execution of a program
java exception handling is managed via five keywords: try, catch, throw, throws, and finally
What is static keyword in java? How it has been used in variables and methods ?
static is a non-access modifier in Java , To create a static member(block,variable,method,nested class), precede its declaration with the keyword static.
What is final and how it has been used variables and methods?
final is a non-access modifier
1.When a variable is declared with final keyword, its value can’t be modified
2.When a class is declared with final keyword, it is called a final class. A final class cannot be extended(inherited).
3.When a method is declared with final keyword, it is called a final method. A final method cannot be overridden.
